cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.SC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a data structure for representing abstract simplicial complexes and its application to mesh generation, which are both topics within computational geometry.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper introduces a new data structure and related algorithms.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible category as the paper presents an example application of the library to represent an orientable surface mesh.
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is a possible category as the paper discusses a data structure for representing abstract simplicial complexes, which can be used in symbolic computation.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the design principles of the data structure and related algorithms, which can be applied to control systems.
